BEGIN:VEVENT
CLASS:Portal
CREATED:20240113T210649Z
DESCRIPTION:Activity 1: Population Growth by CountryThe global population 
 is currently just over 7 billion and is expected to rise to nearly 10 bil
 lion people by 2050. The growth\, however is uneven\, with some countries
  also declining in population. Rapidly rising populations in some countri
 es will suffer in terms of the availability of necessary resources. Decli
 ning populations have their own set of potential future issues with which
  to deal. For this activity\, you will investigate population growth and 
 the resulting impacts on a selected country. To complete this activity\, 
 follow the steps below.  Select any country that appeals to you - be it y
 our home country\, that of your relatives\, or simply one that interests 
 you.Write a maximum 500 word (not including citations) summary about the 
 population growth of your selected country and the impact of that growth 
 on the environment and economy\, keeping in mind what was discussed in cl
 ass. You should use scientific literature to support your discussion. You
  can use the following questions to help guide you\, but feel free to dis
 cuss any other topics related to population growth and its environmental 
 impacts:Find the population growth rate of your home country or any count
 ry of interest to you. Calculate the doubling time based on that growth r
 ate. In what year\, will the population double (if it is indeed growing)?
  You can begin your data search here: https://www.prb.org/international/ 
 (https://www.prb.org/international/) but feel free to use other legitimat
 e sources. Do not forget to cite your sources.Find the demographics break
 down by age group of the country\, especially the number of children vers
 us elderly. You can begin your data search here: https://ourworldindata.o
 rg/age-structure (https://ourworldindata.org/age-structure) but feel free
  to use other legitimate sources. Do not forget to cite your sources. Doe
 s this align with what the growth rate and doubling time tell you? How? A
 re there any economical concerns with this breakdown of age groups?What a
 re the biggest resource concerns for that country? What resources would b
 e sufficient to cover its population growth? Are there any resource conce
 rns if the population is declining? Are there are already environmental c
 oncerns in that country due to population size? What are the potential en
 vironmental consequences of such population growth or decline?Cite your r
 eferences according to APA style format. You can use this guide to help: 
 https://www.mendeley.com/guides/apa-citation-guide/ (https://www.mendeley
 .com/guides/apa-citation-guide/)Submit your 500 word summary in the Dropb
 ox folder here (/d2l/common/dialogs/quickLink/quickLink.d2l?ou=988785&amp
 \;type=dropbox&amp\;rcode=uWaterloo-4230228).You will be graded by the TA
  according to thisRubric (/d2l/common/dialogs/quickLink/quickLink.d2l?ou=
 988785&amp\;type=rubric&amp\;rCode=uWaterloo-3800617).
DTEND;TZID=Etc/UTC:20240118T045900
DTSTAMP:20240113T210649Z
DTSTART;TZID=Etc/UTC:20240118T045900
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Activity 1
UID:3559e8e0-7f1f-45f3-8e8d-43e40b3ea30c
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CLASS:Portal
CREATED:20240113T210649Z
DESCRIPTION:Submit the Population Growth writing activity here. Your grade
  will be based on the rubric you have seen. Equal points per category for
  a total of 25 points possible. \nTurnitin will be used for this Dropbox 
 submission. If you would like to opt out of it\, contact Prof. DelSontro 
 or the TA directly.
DTEND;TZID=Etc/UTC:20240118T045959
