DESCRIPTION:Radio broadcasting did something very unprecedented with mass 
 media – it took hold of people's attention inside their private homes and
  vehicles\, but they could not "skip" ads or information they didn't care
  to hear. What are some things that family units would have been newly ex
 posed to as a result? Why were people so willing to let external voices f
 lood into their homes and vehicles\, and what were they giving up?
DTEND;TZID=Etc/UTC:20240123T050100
