CLASS:Portal
CREATED:20240113T210649Z
DESCRIPTION:From Chapter 3 of New Media\, technological determinism sees s
 ocial change as driven by technological change. As in\, society changes b
 ecause new technologies disrupt society and alter human behaviour. The te
 xtbook asks whether a cluster of technologies can shape historical develo
 pments long-term\, and whether technological devices that are widely adop
 ted and used acquire a sense of "lock-in." How much do you think new tech
 nologies determine social and cultural development? Give at least one exa
 mple.
