DESCRIPTION:Chapter 5 of the textbook suggests that creation is the new co
 nsumption. Ever since platforms like YouTube\, Instagram and Tik Tok beca
 me popular\, consumers have found it easy to shift into becoming producer
 s. However\, it seems as if today\, people often spend more time consumin
 g\, liking\, and sharing content than actually creating new content. How 
 do you define "participatory" culture? With so many people interested in 
 gaining social capital and becoming influencers\, what are they really pr
 oducing?
