BEGIN:VEVENT
CLASS:Portal
CREATED:20240113T210649Z
DESCRIPTION:Gladwell claims the new tools of social media have reinvented 
 social activism. In what ways have social activism changed\, for better o
 r for worse? He also argues that weak ties rarely lead to high-risk activ
 ism. Why is this the case\, and does this mean that weak ties online are 
 less effective than high-risk social ties that affect people in physical 
 protests? Alternatively\, do you believe that Rosenblatt gives too much c
 redit to what Gladwell calls "slacktivism?" How do you feel about the shi
 ft in online culture\, that sees the voices of the youth being amplified 
 more than ever?
DTEND;TZID=Etc/UTC:20240227T050100
DTSTAMP:20240113T210649Z
