BEGIN:VEVENT
CLASS:Portal
CREATED:20240113T210649Z
DESCRIPTION:In this essay\, Harris blames software developers for designin
 g smartphones to be addictive\, and suggests that users are being manipul
 ated without their knowledge. Do you believe people are as unaware as Har
 ris suggests\, and that they don't realize that conveniences come at the 
 cost of their attention? Do you think that smartphone designs are merely 
 complying with what people expect their devices to do for them? Is the on
 us on individuals to monitor their own digital participation\, or are the
  designers to blame\, like Harris argues?
DTEND;TZID=Etc/UTC:20240312T040100
