DESCRIPTION:In the first article\, Turkle argues that the mere presence of
  a smartphone on a table will prevent people from engaging in a meaningfu
 l and thoughtful discussion\, due to the anticipation of being interrupte
 d by a notification. Do you think this is true? Is the presence of a comm
 unicaton device always threatening to divert our attention from the physi
 cal space we are occupying\, or can it add to that same space and draw pe
 ople together?
